## How to integrate (drop-in)

1. Copy `drivers/*.c` and `drivers/*.h` into your Vitis application sources.
2. Copy `tests/*_test.c` if you want the self-tests.
3. Include the header(s) and call the init + operations, e.g.:

```c
{% for unit in units %}{% if unit.transport != 'i2c_mux' %}#include "{{ unit.module }}.h"
{% endif %}{% endfor %}

/* ... after your BSP is up ... */
{% for unit in units %}{% if unit.transport != 'i2c_mux' %}/* {{ unit.part }}: */
{% for n in unit.public_names %}{{ n }}(...);
{% endfor %}{% endif %}{% endfor %}```

> The drivers initialize their own controller instance via `XIicPs_LookupConfig` /
> `XSpiPs_LookupConfig` using the `xparameters.h` device IDs. Mux-attached devices select
> their channel automatically before each access.
